 :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">Ω</span> → <span class=\"fn\">ι</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Hitting time: given a stochastic process `u` and a set `s`, `hittingBtwn u s n m` is\nthe first time `u` is in `s` after time `n` and before time `m` (if `u` does not hit `s`\nafter time `n` and before `m` then the hitting time is simply `m`).\n\nThe hitting time is a stopping time if the process is strongly adapted and discrete. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Process/HittingTime.html#MeasureTheory.hittingBtwn","kind":"def","line":51,"name":"MeasureTheory.hittingBtwn","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Probability/Process/HittingTime.lean#L51-L59"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Probability.Process.Stopping","Mathlib.Tactic.AdaptationNote"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Probability.Process.HittingTime"}